  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "This is an issue for the bug where the validator client crashes if the beacon chain node it is watching goes offline for any reason before the validators activation epoch. \r\n\r\nOnce the validator is activated it retries the connection just fine as it should. However the client should have this behavior pre-activation as well.\r\n\r\nAnd example of the error log is:\r\n```\r\n[2019-04-12 23:19:51] FATAL validator: Could not wait for validator activation: could not receive validator activation from stream: rpc error: code = Unknown desc = rpc context closed, exiting goroutine\r\n```",
